sub_title: Editor@Brill (Active Profile): Material Cultures, Art History, Archeology, Architecture, Middle East & Islamic Studies, Mediterranean Art Histories, Sensory History, Literary Cultures, Indian Ocean Cultures & Networks
summary:
Culture is valuable. It is what binds us and makes us human. 
It is a privilege to offer a scholarly platform to our diverse, international community of authors, editors and publishing partners. Their important, innovative, and multi-disciplinary research not only informs many academic fields, but also the decisions of policy makers, heritage professionals, and eventually also mainstream media, popular culture, and people's understanding of cultures, histories, and identities (including their own). 
 
I love to connect with people, bring them together, and start and develop new collaborations and publishing initiatives. Creative, inquisitive, flexible, out-of-the-box thinker. Culturally sensitive, diplomatic, solution and goal oriented. I value authenticity, empathy, integrity, transparancy and a personable approach. 

"Love many things, for therein lies the true strength,  and whosoever loves much, performs much, and can accomplish much, and what is done in love is done well."

Email: Teddi.Dols@Brill.com; 
teddidols@gmail.com
